HEADWORD: Armlet
<hw>Arm"let</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Arm</ets> +
<ets>-let</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small arm; <as>as, an
<ex>armlet</ex> of the sea</as>.</def> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An arm ring; a bracelet for the upper arm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Armor for the arm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Armoniac</ent>⟦br⟧
